BIRTHDAY MUNNINGS was hustled early trying for better inside position, could not quicken enough on the rail and was shuffled back to trail at the half, could see the field under a hard ride through the turn making little headway and passed a tiring runner in the final furlong. SPARKLET was brushed outside on the break, travelled in the third flight three deep outside foes down the backside, began to lengthen stride three wide midpoint on the turn to be in the mix at the top of the lane for a share and was outfinished late settling for a minor role in the end. HALCON NEGRO stalked three wide in midpack down the back straight, made little headway on rivals through the turn and finished up with intent outside gaining positions in the final furlong. MUCHO MAGNIFICO was void of speed trailing down the backstretch, ran far behind the field through the turn and finished up with good late energy passing rivals in the final sixteenth. COMPUTER HACKER travelled in the third flight in the two path in the beginning, was urged with foes on each side midway on the turn keeping pace to be in the mix for a share turning for home and yielded while drifting in in the last eighth. SAMURAI CHALLENGE broke in at the start, stalked near the rear three wide down the back straight away, was hard ridden on the rail around the bend making little advance, lost its path behind a tiring rival at the furlong marker and had little finish afterwards. STILL WICKED chased the frontrunning winner down the backside, was urged on the fence at the five sixteenths pole, offered a mild run until top of the lane and retreated on the fence in mid stretch.

MR. DE had a good position on the rail watching the front duo at the half, waited to pounce while nestled on the rail throughout the turn, could not find another gear straightening out for the drive behind runners to pose a serious threat for the win but finished up with energy between horses to be involved in the photo for third at the wire. PREETZAH'S STAR hounded the pace outside down the back straight, had a brief lead poking his head in front midpoint on the turn, could not hold off the outside runners making a bid turning for home, battled stubbornly on the wrong lead through the stretch and faded nearing the wire losing positions at the finish. BLASITO dictated terms up front down the backside on the rail, was collared outside midway through the turn, was urged on the fence trying to maintain position at the top of the stretch and backed away inside in the final furlong. JUST THE MAX could see the field at the half, began to pick up horses three wide two furlongs out and showed late interest down the stretch to pass tired foes in the final furlong. GOOD SKIP INDEED was bumped inside to begin, stalked four deep close to the rear in the early going, was roused three wide outside for more run three furlongs from the finish, made little progress on the turn and could not be a presence running down the lane. WONT FORGET YOU was bumped on the break outside, settled three wide near the back of the pack at the half, stalled between rivals while getting out at the quarter pole and could not regroup on the rail down the stretch to be a factor. SEATTLE POINT was in the second flight tracking in the two path between runners down the back straight, could not accelerate with others into the turn losing inside position, gave way with five sixteenths to go and was not involved driving to the finish.
